--- [indian-med-africa] iter 27 | added=7 | Fri May 22 12:08:40 EDT 2026 ---
DONE: Manta Point Bangaram added successfully

Added the most-dived site in Lakshadweep (India) — Manta Point on the outer reef of Bangaram Atoll at 10.95°N, 72.32°E, 6–23 m. Lakshadweep had 0 sites; this is the canonical first entry. Set `heroImageUrl: null` because no genuinely site-specific underwater image of Bangaram's reef exists on Wikimedia Commons — the available Lakshadweep imagery is from other atolls (Minicoy, Kavaratti) and would be a stand-in. Committed as `2a4f354` and pushed.

Sources:
- [Bangaram Atoll - Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangaram_Atoll)
- [Diving in Lakshadweep | PADI](https://www.padi.com/diving-in/lakshadweep/)
- [Bangaram Dive Center | PADI](https://www.padi.com/dive-center/india/bangaram-dive-center/)
- [Lakshadweep: India's Best Kept Secret | PADI Blog](https://blog.padi.com/lakshadweep-indias-best-kept-secret/)
