--- [indian-med-africa] iter 31 | added=11 | Fri May 22 12:33:56 EDT 2026 ---
DONE: Conshelf II (Précontinent II) added successfully

Added the remains of Jacques Cousteau's 1963 underwater habitat at Shaab Rumi, Sudan — sub hangar at 10 m (still holds original air pocket), shark cage at 27 m, tool shed and fish cages encrusted with coral. Hero image is a 4608×3456 underwater photo from Wikimedia Commons showing the actual hangar structure. Mapped to existing `sudan-shaab-rumi` location, editorial rank 86. Featured in Cousteau's Oscar-winning "World Without Sun."

Sources:
- [Continental Shelf Station Two — Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continental_Shelf_Station_Two)
- [Précontinent II — Atlas Obscura](https://www.atlasobscura.com/places/precontinent-ii)
- [Wikimedia Commons — Category:Conshelf](https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Conshelf)
- [Sha'ab Rumi coordinates — getamap.net](https://www.getamap.net/maps/sudan/(su31)/_rumi_shaab/)
